                     <interp inst="t17720429-53-person464" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . A little after seven at night, I saw a man attempting to break into <placeName id="t17720429-53-crimeloc261">Smart's Key</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17720429-53-crimeloc261" type="placeName" value="Smart's Key"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17720429-53-crimeloc261" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720429-53-off259 t17720429-53-crimeloc261"></join>; I don't know whether it was the prisoner; I told my master Mr. Jefferson of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17720429-53-person465">
                  Thomas
                   Charnock
               <interp inst="t17720429-53-person465" type="surname" value="Charnock"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720429-53-person465" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720429-53-person465" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner at the bottom of Smart's Key; he had no hat on, this hat I saw him wear the same day.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I know nothing of this; as to my hat I dropped it into the river; I am entirely innocent of the charge.</p>
